        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP-INTEGRATION\n*Module*: SYSTEM\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP-INTEGRATION\n*Phase*: INTEGRATION_ASSEMBLY\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"SYSTEM\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"### ACTIVE REGRESSION DETECTED\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"failed\\\",\\n  \\\"phase_completed\\\": \\\"INTEGRATION_TESTING\\\",\\n  \\\"regression_reason\\\": \\\"LOGIC_MISMATCH and MISSING_FEATURES: The ui-gateway is a generic placeholder. It lacks the Fund Selector, Timeframe Toggle, and the 'Built by SDLC-Factory' footer required by PROD_SPEC.md. Furthermore, it fetches '/api/data' which returns a 404, causing the React app to crash with 't.forEach is not a function'. The logic-api provides '/api/heatmap' but returns a dummy 2D array '[[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]]' which is not formatted for @nivo/heatmap. The CODING phase failed to implement the required features and API contracts.\\\",\\n  \\\"e2e_metrics\\\": {\\n    \\\"scenarios_executed\\\": 4,\\n    \\\"critical_paths_passed\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n\\n```\\n\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\\nStack: Docker Compose, React/Vite (pnpm), Python (uv), PostgreSQL\\nEntry_Point: http://localhost:8000\\nInterface_Mount_Selector: #root\\nINTEGRATION_TEST_CMD: cd ui-gateway && pnpm install && npx playwright install chromium && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list\\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\\n\\n\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"No legacy semantic snippet queries found for this module.\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"### Historic Insight (coder)\\n**Context**: [Python/uv] Build fails with hatchling due to missing README.md\\n**Resolution**:\\n```\\nWhen building a Python package with `uv pip install --system .` and `hatchling`, ensure that the `README.md` file exists if it is referenced in `pyproject.toml`, otherwise the build will fail with `OSError: Readme file does not exist: README.md`.\\n```\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"status\",\n    \"phase_completed\",\n    \"module_id\",\n    \"execution_metrics\",\n    \"artifacts\",\n    \"qa_handoff\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"status\": {\n      \"const\": \"success\"\n    },\n    \"phase_completed\": {\n      \"const\": \"INTEGRATION_ASSEMBLY\"\n    },\n    \"module_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"execution_metrics\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\n        \"tool_calls_made\",\n        \"compilation_passed\"\n      ],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"tool_calls_made\": {\n          \"type\": \"number\"\n        },\n        \"compilation_passed\": {\n          \"const\": true\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"artifacts\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\"\n    },\n    \"qa_handoff\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\n        \"test_target\",\n        \"exec_command\"\n      ],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"test_target\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"exec_command\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n",
